### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api

### 1. Signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get Current User (Protected)
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Create Folder (Protected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/folders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "My Documents"
}

### 5. Get Folders (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/folders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Upload File (Protected)
# Note: You'll need to specify a real file path if using VS Code REST Client
POST {{baseUrl}}/files/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Hello DriveStack! This is a test file.
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="folder_id"

{{folder_id}}
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 7. Get File Download Link (Protected)
@file_id = your-file-id-here
GET {{baseUrl}}/files/{{file_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Create Share Link (Protected)
# Returns a token that can be used by ANYONE publically
POST {{baseUrl}}/files/{{file_id}}/share
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "expiresInHours": 1
}

### 9. Retrieve File from Public Share Link (Public)
# No Authorization header needed!
@share_token = your-share-token-here
GET {{baseUrl}}/share/{{share_token}}
